  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of the study is to investigate pain, anxiety and depression in chronic pain
      patients with and without neuropathic pain compared with healthy volunteers
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Primary outcome measures:

        -  Symptom checklist 92

      Secondary outcome measures:

        -  Hamilton Depression and Anxiety Rating Scale

        -  Major Depression Inventory

        -  GAD-10 Anxiety Scale

        -  Health Survey SF-36

        -  McGill Pain Questionnaire

        -  Sweat test

        -  Heart rate variability testing

        -  Coping Strategy Questionnare

        -  Quantitative sensory testing

        -  Pain Catastrophizing Scale

        -  Pain rating (VAS)

        -  Interview
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
